{"build_type":"library","description":"Struct-returning core of the Vehir firmware and the single source of every firmware value. Probes the host hybrid topology and RAM, applies the resource lock (three-slot struct perf_req eff_req arena_req at lock_ptr; zero in a slot means take the host ceiling for that axis), clamps each axis, derives the granted per-class affinity masks, and writes a 14-slot envelope into out_struct: 0 granted_arena_bytes, 1 granted_cores, 2 granted_threads, 3 granted_perf_mask, 4 granted_eff_mask, 5 perf_tpc, 6 eff_tpc, 7 host_ram_bytes, 8 host_perf_cores, 9 host_eff_cores, 10 host_perf_mask, 11 host_eff_mask, 12 granted_perf_cores, 13 granted_eff_cores. Both the JSON firmware tool and the boot driver call this so probe and clamp live in one place. lock_ptr must be a valid three-slot struct; out_struct must be at least 112 bytes.","module_name":"derive-firmware-resource-handoff-envelope","package_name":"derive-firmware-resource-handoff-envelope","function_definitions":{"derive-firmware-resource-handoff-envelope":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"cpuinfo_path","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"lock_ptr","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"out_struct","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instructio